-- National Geographic Crew Killed in Copter Crash
-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 2012-02-05T10:53:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/national-geographic-crew-killed-in-copter-crash.html
U.S. cinematographer Mike deGruy and
Australian television writer-producer Andrew Wight have died in
a helicopter crash in eastern  Australia , the  Associated Press 
said, citing their employer National Geographic.  Police said an Australian helicopter pilot and his U.S.
passenger died at the scene soon after takeoff from an airstrip
near Nowra, 97 miles (156 kilometers) north of Sydney, the  news
agency  said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Mike Harrison  at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  